-- Altair Provides Battery Storage System to Puerto Rico Solar Farm
-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 2012-10-03T15:46:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-03/altair-provides-battery-storage-system-to-puerto-rico-solar-farm.html
Altair Nanotechnologies Inc. (ALTI) , a U.S.
maker of  lithium-ion batteries , agreed to sell a 2-megawatt
storage system for a solar farm in Puerto Rico.  The system will be installed at the 26-megawatt San Fermin
solar project that Uriel Renewables Inc. and Coqui Power LLC are
jointly developing, Reno, Nevada-based Altair said today in a
statement. Terms weren’t disclosed.  Canadian Solar Inc. said yesterday it’s supplying panels
for the project.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ehren Goossens in New York at 
 egoossens1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
